item.description:
There are three ways you can declare and assign in JS in 2020:
let a = &quot;Hello&quot; var b = &quot;World&quot; const c = &quot;!&quot; These are &ldquo;declarations with assignment&rdquo;, as opposed to &ldquo;declaration without assignment&rdquo; - which can only be done with let and var:
let a; var b; const c; // has no meaning To understand the difference between let and var, you can refer to this excellent answer on StackOverflow.
